window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>\"A full master of the epic fantasy.\" (</b><b><i>Tulsa World</i></b><b>)</b></p> <p>One of the world’s most acclaimed fantasists, <i>New York Times</i> best-selling author Robin Hobb returns to the world of her popular Tawny Man trilogy with <i>Dragon Haven</i> - the second book, following <i>Dragon Keeper</i> (\"Imaginative, literate, and compassionate from first page to last\" (<i>Booklist</i>)) in an epic adventure about the resurgence of dragons in a world that both needs and fears them.</p> <p>Hobb, whose Soldier Son trilogy (<i>Shaman’s Crossing</i>, <i>Forest Mage</i>, <i>Renegade’s Magic</i>) has won raves from critics, fans, and peers alike, returns to the Rain Wilds with <i>Dragon Haven</i>, and fans of Raymond Feist, Terry Brooks, and Lois McMaster Bujold will eagerly follow.</p>"; 
